WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:11.205 --> 00:00:12.800
Shine those lights!

2
00:00:12.825 --> 00:00:14.870
- Let's go! Lock it down!
- I got it!

3
00:00:14.895 --> 00:00:16.240
Watch out! Brace! It's a big one!

4
00:00:20.144 --> 00:00:21.646
Man! Oh. no!

5
00:00:22.006 --> 00:00:23.473
We're getting hammered out here!

6
00:00:23.573 --> 00:00:25.178
Everything up!

7
00:00:25.345 --> 00:00:27.318
Nets coming up!

8
00:00:27.774 --> 00:00:29.536
- Bring it in!
- Steady!

9
00:00:29.628 --> 00:00:30.962
Pull!

10
00:00:36.609 --> 00:00:37.651
What the hell? -

11
00:00:37.676 --> 00:00:39.652
Is there somethin' in there?

12
00:00:42.157 --> 00:00:44.495
It's big! It... It's moving!

13
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.579
- <i> Chris!</i>
<i>-  No! It's right there!</i>

14
00:00:51.582 --> 00:00:53.668
Chris! Let's take 'em out!

15
00:00:56.015 --> 00:00:57.304
Shark?

16
00:00:57.474 --> 00:00:58.862
That ain't no shark!

17
00:00:58.957 --> 00:01:01.667
Xander? You see it?
It's over there!

18
00:01:03.742 --> 00:01:05.947
Come on. come on. where are you at?

19
00:01:05.972 --> 00:01:07.248
Show yourself.

20
00:01:09.878 --> 00:01:11.552
- Oh!
- Chris! Watch out!

21
00:01:11.590 --> 00:01:12.988
Comin' around!

22
00:01:13.015 --> 00:01:14.899
Goin' your way. Cal!
Calvin. head it off!

23
00:01:14.924 --> 00:01:16.160
In the hold! Get it down there!

24
00:01:16.185 --> 00:01:18.950
Get it down there!

25
00:01:19.866 --> 00:01:20.997
What the hell is it?

26
00:01:21.022 --> 00:01:23.405
- Oh. Xander!
- Chris.

27
00:01:23.817 --> 00:01:25.479
- God. Xander!
- Chris!

28
00:01:25.831 --> 00:01:27.480
Oh. God!

29
00:01:31.409 --> 00:01:32.774
Come on!

30
00:01:33.138 --> 00:01:34.477
He's lost a lot of blood. but...

31
00:01:34.502 --> 00:01:36.802
Tamp it down.
Get in there good and tight.

32
00:01:38.522 --> 00:01:42.420
This is the<i> North Star.</i>
vessel number 53422N.

33
00:01:42.515 --> 00:01:43.716
I have a crew member in need of

34
00:01:43.740 --> 00:01:45.577
immediate medical evacuation. Over.

35
00:01:45.756 --> 00:01:47.722
- <i>Nature of injury?</i>
- Bite to the abdomen.

36
00:01:47.784 --> 00:01:49.413
severe blood loss. Over.

37
00:01:49.478 --> 00:01:50.891
<i>What bit him?</i>

38
00:01:51.398 --> 00:01:53.057
I...

39
00:01:53.425 --> 00:01:55.433
I got no idea.

40
00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:03.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

41
00:02:27.749 --> 00:02:29.547
What is it?

42
00:03:00.551 --> 00:03:01.550
Secure.

43
00:03:03.851 --> 00:03:06.406
Let's see what you
caught tonight. Captain.

44
00:03:06.992 --> 00:03:09.138
What I caught is none of your business!

45
00:03:09.185 --> 00:03:11.070
You're just here
for my injured crewman.

46
00:03:11.163 --> 00:03:12.382
Of course.

47
00:03:12.429 --> 00:03:14.200
We'll be needing him as well.

48
00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:17.260
Let's go!

49
00:03:21.330 --> 00:03:23.326
Now then. Captain...

50
00:03:23.386 --> 00:03:25.196
I'm entitled to that catch!

51
00:03:41.636 --> 00:03:43.122
Let's go!

52
00:04:26.341 --> 00:04:28.340
Look what we found!

53
00:04:28.516 --> 00:04:29.716
Margaritas!

54
00:04:29.741 --> 00:04:31.839
Whoo!

55
00:04:32.774 --> 00:04:35.319
Do you want a pretzel?!

56
00:04:39.227 --> 00:04:42.808
It was more than 150 years ago

57
00:04:42.875 --> 00:04:44.719
when a local fishing captain.

58
00:04:44.786 --> 00:04:48.038
Charles H. Pownall.
fell in love with a mermaid

59
00:04:48.091 --> 00:04:49.770
in these very waters.

60
00:04:49.916 --> 00:04:52.700
enchanted by her beautiful Siren song.

61
00:04:52.747 --> 00:04:54.258
I love you. fisherman.

62
00:04:54.293 --> 00:04:55.425
I love you. mermaid.

63
00:04:55.460 --> 00:04:58.061
But one day. he went to the bay.

64
00:04:58.147 --> 00:05:00.179
and his mermaid was gone

65
00:05:00.328 --> 00:05:02.113
back to her home in the sea.

66
00:05:02.173 --> 00:05:03.644
never to return.

67
00:05:03.758 --> 00:05:06.888
And that is how.
thanks to Charles H. Pownall.

68
00:05:06.982 --> 00:05:10.230
Bristol Cove became the
Mermaid Capital of the World.

69
00:05:17.992 --> 00:05:20.166
Wow. Thank you.

70
00:05:21.003 --> 00:05:24.902
That was my great-great-great-
grandfather depicted there.

71
00:05:24.927 --> 00:05:26.286
so as you can see. our family goes back

72
00:05:26.311 --> 00:05:28.125
a long ways in Bristol Cove.

73
00:05:28.169 --> 00:05:31.051
Now please allow me to introduce
my beautiful wife Elaine

74
00:05:31.076 --> 00:05:33.420
and our two wonderful sons.
Doug and Ben.

75
00:05:37.472 --> 00:05:38.764
It seems. uh.

76
00:05:38.799 --> 00:05:40.897
Ben may have been caught up
in the parade traffic.

77
00:05:40.984 --> 00:05:43.308
but I can assure you
he is here in spirit.

78
00:05:43.400 --> 00:05:46.202
So to all the good people
of Bristol Cove.

79
00:05:46.247 --> 00:05:49.246
it is our great honor
to bestow this monument

80
00:05:49.355 --> 00:05:52.220
to one of our town's founding fathers.

81
00:05:52.316 --> 00:05:55.281
Charles H. Pownall.

82
00:06:01.039 --> 00:06:03.323
Where the hell's Ben? Hmm?

83
00:06:21.517 --> 00:06:23.809
Hola! How'd it go?

84
00:06:24.276 --> 00:06:25.744
Rescued a Steller.

85
00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:27.075
She's in pretty bad shape.

86
00:06:27.100 --> 00:06:28.828
She's tagged. She's one of ours.

87
00:06:28.853 --> 00:06:31.099
- Where'd you find her?
- Out by Scott's Point.

88
00:06:31.124 --> 00:06:32.410
That's pretty far.

89
00:06:32.435 --> 00:06:33.567
Yeah. about 30 miles

90
00:06:33.592 --> 00:06:34.858
outside her usual range.

91
00:06:34.982 --> 00:06:36.600
Probably looking for food.

92
00:06:39.305 --> 00:06:40.583
Don't worry. girl.

93
00:06:40.618 --> 00:06:41.983
We're gonna take good care of you.

94
00:06:44.451 --> 00:06:46.415
Come on.

95
00:06:49.303 --> 00:06:50.903
She's starving out there.

96
00:06:50.944 --> 00:06:52.404
It's a good thing we went out today.

97
00:06:52.438 --> 00:06:53.920
Not sure your dad
would agree with that.

98
00:06:53.945 --> 00:06:56.710
Well. I'll add that to the list
of things we don't agree on.

99
00:06:56.780 --> 00:06:58.429
Like you and me being together?

100
00:06:58.466 --> 00:07:00.148
Hey. Look.

101
00:07:00.200 --> 00:07:03.417
if I did everything my dad told me.

102
00:07:03.594 --> 00:07:05.493
well. I'd be my brother.

103
00:07:05.977 --> 00:07:07.358
You want to come over later?

104
00:07:07.436 --> 00:07:09.401
I promised my dad I'd make him dinner.

105
00:07:09.763 --> 00:07:11.581
Third time this week?

106
00:07:11.743 --> 00:07:13.874
- Lucky guy.
- He needs me.

107
00:07:13.912 --> 00:07:15.855
He'd be at the drive-thru
every night if I didn't cook.

108
00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:17.812
Seriously. it's disturbing.

109
00:07:18.559 --> 00:07:20.958
I could come by after for dessert.

110
00:07:21.311 --> 00:07:22.786
Spend the night?

111
00:07:23.267 --> 00:07:24.565
If you want me to.

112
00:07:24.641 --> 00:07:26.239
What do you think?

113
00:07:35.443 --> 00:07:38.686
Hey. man. Thought you guys
were out past Bowers Ridge.

114
00:07:38.739 --> 00:07:40.731
- You're back early.
- Yeah.

115
00:07:40.802 --> 00:07:42.845
I need to talk to you about something.

116
00:07:43.467 --> 00:07:44.701
All right.

117
00:07:44.748 --> 00:07:45.993
Boys.

118
00:07:47.970 --> 00:07:50.614
We said keep this between us.
Don't tell anybody.

119
00:07:50.650 --> 00:07:52.390
Ben knows about this stuff. all right?

120
00:07:52.437 --> 00:07:53.682
He can help us.

121
00:07:54.136 --> 00:07:56.401
- He's one of us.
- He wasn't on the boat with us.

122
00:07:56.458 --> 00:07:58.289
He doesn't fish with us no more.

123
00:08:04.082 --> 00:08:05.785
We caught somethin' out there.

124
00:08:05.820 --> 00:08:07.370
I mean. it's just somethin' we...

125
00:08:07.610 --> 00:08:09.387
we ain't never seen before.

126
00:08:09.865 --> 00:08:11.263
It attacked Chris.

127
00:08:11.288 --> 00:08:12.429
He had to get airlifted out.

128
00:08:12.454 --> 00:08:14.709
big-ass military commando helicopter.

129
00:08:14.834 --> 00:08:16.832
Navy SEALs. the whole deal.

130
00:08:17.028 --> 00:08:19.893
CG says they have
no record of the evac.

131
00:08:20.062 --> 00:08:21.714
like it never happened.

132
00:08:21.780 --> 00:08:23.181
He's just gone.

133
00:08:23.379 --> 00:08:25.248
What do you mean he's gone?

134
00:08:25.591 --> 00:08:27.612
You really don't know
what attacked him?

135
00:08:36.532 --> 00:08:37.664
A mermaid?

136
00:08:37.871 --> 00:08:39.363
It didn't look like that. okay?

137
00:08:39.388 --> 00:08:42.354
This... this was a predator.

138
00:08:45.167 --> 00:08:47.054
Okay. that was a good one.

139
00:08:47.995 --> 00:08:49.437
Yeah. very. very well done.

140
00:08:49.462 --> 00:08:50.509
You almost had me there.

141
00:08:50.534 --> 00:08:52.433
Dude. this is real.

142
00:08:52.756 --> 00:08:55.155
Hey. why else would they
take it from us. huh?

143
00:08:55.476 --> 00:08:57.050
Wait.

144
00:08:58.852 --> 00:09:00.363
Here. Look.

145
00:09:00.791 --> 00:09:02.689
Okay.

146
00:09:07.564 --> 00:09:09.233
Xander. man. this could be anything.

147
00:09:10.968 --> 00:09:13.867
I don't know what you call it.

148
00:09:14.003 --> 00:09:17.935
but. trust me. it's not
what you think it is.

149
00:09:29.445 --> 00:09:31.277
<i> We had a report six weeks ago.</i>

150
00:09:31.302 --> 00:09:33.375
Japanese fishermen claimed
they saw a sea creature

151
00:09:33.400 --> 00:09:34.643
off the Kuril Islands.

152
00:09:34.687 --> 00:09:36.828
Then some carcasses
washed ashore in Alaska

153
00:09:36.928 --> 00:09:38.926
with strange bite marks all over them.

154
00:09:39.142 --> 00:09:40.866
Then five days ago. our research vessel

155
00:09:40.891 --> 00:09:42.337
picked up unidentified frequencies

156
00:09:42.362 --> 00:09:43.847
coming from the Bering Strait.

157
00:09:44.427 --> 00:09:45.765
We knew something was out there.

158
00:09:45.870 --> 00:09:47.488
That's when I alerted your people.

159
00:09:47.707 --> 00:09:50.082
And you're sure this is
what you think it is?

160
00:09:50.139 --> 00:09:51.590
Well. Admiral...

161
00:09:51.618 --> 00:09:54.268
...why don't you judge for yourself?

162
00:10:20.219 --> 00:10:21.750
Good morning. dear.

163
00:10:23.086 --> 00:10:26.012
Your father is terribly angry with you.

164
00:10:26.187 --> 00:10:28.719
Good morning to you. too.

165
00:10:29.396 --> 00:10:31.054
Anthony?

166
00:10:31.523 --> 00:10:33.822
I don't give a rat's ass
if your father's angry.

167
00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:35.914
A lot of things make him angry.

168
00:10:36.112 --> 00:10:37.977
like the fact that a woman
who can't walk

169
00:10:38.002 --> 00:10:40.422
insists on buying $600 shoes.

170
00:10:40.844 --> 00:10:42.368
You know what he called
me the other day?

171
00:10:42.393 --> 00:10:44.824
- What?
- Bitch on wheels.

172
00:10:46.281 --> 00:10:49.020
- That's actually pretty funny.
- I thought so. too.

173
00:10:50.654 --> 00:10:52.653
Do you know why it was okay?

174
00:10:52.805 --> 00:10:55.101
Because it was behind closed doors.

175
00:10:55.756 --> 00:10:57.057
Family rule...

176
00:10:57.165 --> 00:10:58.471
You can say whatever the hell

177
00:10:58.496 --> 00:10:59.818
awful thing you want in private.

178
00:10:59.843 --> 00:11:01.222
but in public...

179
00:11:02.765 --> 00:11:05.764
This is a face that keeps
Mommy in nice shoes.

180
00:11:06.980 --> 00:11:09.205
- I get it.
- No. I don't think you do.

181
00:11:10.168 --> 00:11:12.726
Because if you did. you'd show up.

182
00:11:13.193 --> 00:11:15.727
You would flash
that famous Pownall charm.

183
00:11:16.516 --> 00:11:18.383
and you wouldn't leave
your father up on stage

184
00:11:18.421 --> 00:11:20.224
with his pants around his ankles.

185
00:11:20.249 --> 00:11:21.695
You know what. Mom?

186
00:11:21.902 --> 00:11:24.662
If you guys want to put a
show on for the whole town.

187
00:11:25.119 --> 00:11:26.663
that's your business. but I...

188
00:11:27.158 --> 00:11:28.989
I don't want anything to do with it.

189
00:11:29.358 --> 00:11:31.357
I got other things to worry about.

190
00:11:32.587 --> 00:11:34.411
The spawning habits
of a bunch of plankton

191
00:11:34.436 --> 00:11:35.609
are more important than family.

192
00:11:35.634 --> 00:11:37.265
That's not what I'm saying.

193
00:11:37.933 --> 00:11:41.496
And I really don't want to
have this conversation again.

194
00:11:42.089 --> 00:11:45.021
Ben. I need this family
to keep working.

195
00:11:46.784 --> 00:11:49.342
And I'm not willing
to suffer for nothing.

196
00:11:52.079 --> 00:11:53.878
Okay. I hear you.

197
00:11:55.832 --> 00:11:59.248
Doug tells me that you're hot
and heavy with Maddie Bishop.

198
00:11:59.372 --> 00:12:01.697
Yeah. we're dating.

199
00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:04.122
You always had a thing
for the wild girls.

200
00:12:04.446 --> 00:12:06.411
I gotta get some stuff done.

201
00:12:12.376 --> 00:12:15.020
Always had a thing
for the wild girls. huh?

202
00:12:15.090 --> 00:12:16.522
I'm sorry.

203
00:12:16.577 --> 00:12:18.176
She didn't know you were in here.

204
00:12:18.472 --> 00:12:19.804
So if it weren't for your brother.

205
00:12:19.839 --> 00:12:22.438
she wouldn't even know
we were seeing each other?

206
00:12:22.541 --> 00:12:24.339
Believe me. with my family.

207
00:12:24.859 --> 00:12:27.385
nothing good ever comes from sharing.

208
00:12:27.618 --> 00:12:30.625
You never know. Your mom and
I might actually hit it off.

209
00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:32.708
Yeah. you might be right.

210
00:12:33.199 --> 00:12:34.751
I mean. you're exactly

211
00:12:34.776 --> 00:12:36.559
the kind of girl she'd
want me to be with.

212
00:12:36.675 --> 00:12:38.576
Oh. yeah? What kind of girl is that?

213
00:12:39.710 --> 00:12:41.575
Beautiful.

214
00:12:42.952 --> 00:12:44.424
Smart.

215
00:12:46.652 --> 00:12:48.384
Funny.

216
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:52.421
Passionate.

217
00:12:54.087 --> 00:12:55.949
And that smile

218
00:12:56.808 --> 00:12:58.515
that could power a small city.

219
00:12:59.332 --> 00:13:01.231
Ah. yes.

220
00:13:01.256 --> 00:13:04.257
Ah. that famous Pownall charm.

221
00:13:17.217 --> 00:13:19.871
Mm! No. dude. Aberdeen.

222
00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:22.264
The best weed is in Aberdeen.

223
00:13:22.306 --> 00:13:25.977
Seriously gourmet Kush.

224
00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:29.305
Even my mom likes it.

225
00:13:29.424 --> 00:13:32.041
I don't remember him being
such a burner in high school.

226
00:13:32.222 --> 00:13:33.853
Yeah. that was more your crowd. right?

227
00:13:33.902 --> 00:13:36.081
Oh. all right. golden boy.

228
00:13:43.979 --> 00:13:46.012
Hey. I'll be back in a minute.

229
00:13:46.234 --> 00:13:47.783
Okay.

230
00:13:54.310 --> 00:13:56.691
I swear I'm gonna kill you
if you go out too far!

231
00:14:02.749 --> 00:14:04.102
Hey.

232
00:14:04.202 --> 00:14:05.681
You okay?

233
00:14:05.811 --> 00:14:08.576
You're not seriously pissed
at me. are you?

234
00:14:08.651 --> 00:14:10.250
I shouldn't have told you.

235
00:14:10.392 --> 00:14:11.556
- Should have known better.
- Think about

236
00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:13.101
what you're asking me to believe.

237
00:14:13.145 --> 00:14:15.241
I get it. You don't come out

238
00:14:15.266 --> 00:14:16.421
on the boat with us anymore.

239
00:14:16.446 --> 00:14:17.923
You weren't there.

240
00:14:18.236 --> 00:14:20.365
They took Chris.

241
00:14:21.094 --> 00:14:22.811
They don't want people
to know about this.

242
00:14:22.836 --> 00:14:25.322
Look. I don't know
what happened to Chris.

243
00:14:26.015 --> 00:14:28.035
Maybe he's in a military hospital.

244
00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:29.786
We're gonna find him. Xan.

245
00:14:29.875 --> 00:14:32.446
This isn't part of some huge cover-up.

246
00:14:32.471 --> 00:14:34.402
and it's not because
of some mythical creature

247
00:14:34.427 --> 00:14:35.880
that you guys think that you caught.

248
00:14:35.905 --> 00:14:37.227
So you're telling me
you know everything

249
00:14:37.251 --> 00:14:39.250
- there is to know about...
- No. of course not!

250
00:14:39.275 --> 00:14:41.040
Then look me in the eye and you tell me

251
00:14:41.065 --> 00:14:42.922
that maybe... maybe there
is something down there

252
00:14:42.947 --> 00:14:44.445
that we haven't seen before.

253
00:14:49.383 --> 00:14:51.681
- Xan...
- Just...

254
00:14:52.247 --> 00:14:53.794
Just do it.

255
00:14:54.846 --> 00:14:56.205
Okay.

256
00:14:56.472 --> 00:14:57.859
Sure.

257
00:14:57.938 --> 00:14:59.869
95% of the oceans remain unexplored.

258
00:14:59.931 --> 00:15:02.796
So it could happen?

259
00:15:06.993 --> 00:15:08.792
Xander. man. I love you.

260
00:15:08.828 --> 00:15:10.024
You know that.

261
00:15:10.058 --> 00:15:12.282
But as a friend. I'm telling you.

262
00:15:12.307 --> 00:15:14.794
you gotta stop talking like this.

263
00:15:16.190 --> 00:15:17.695
What would it take?

264
00:15:18.697 --> 00:15:20.163
Hmm?

265
00:15:20.343 --> 00:15:21.642
For you to believe me?

266
00:15:23.010 --> 00:15:24.575
I'd have to see one.

267
00:15:30.113 --> 00:15:31.555
That's it.

268
00:15:33.361 --> 00:15:34.944
That's exactly right.

269
00:15:36.294 --> 00:15:38.126
We gotta catch another one.

270
00:15:39.884 --> 00:15:41.715
Lucas. get back here!

271
00:16:02.583 --> 00:16:04.487
Shark! Shark! Shark!

272
00:16:04.530 --> 00:16:06.529
Aah! Aah!

273
00:16:06.845 --> 00:16:08.143
Shark!

274
00:16:08.305 --> 00:16:10.843
Shark!

275
00:16:15.059 --> 00:16:16.464
What are you thinking?

276
00:16:20.484 --> 00:16:22.002
I can't even believe it.

277
00:16:22.070 --> 00:16:24.903
It's disgusting.

278
00:16:26.560 --> 00:16:29.814
This damage definitely
wasn't inflicted by an orca.

279
00:16:30.061 --> 00:16:32.192
The bite radius is way too small.

280
00:16:32.721 --> 00:16:34.187
So what then?

281
00:16:34.293 --> 00:16:36.545
Well. it's not another shark.

282
00:16:36.752 --> 00:16:38.504
There are a million explanations.

283
00:16:38.684 --> 00:16:40.917
- Okay?
- Caught in a boat prop.

284
00:16:40.977 --> 00:16:43.241
sea lion bit the carcass?

285
00:16:45.639 --> 00:16:48.231
What if there's
a new predator out there?

286
00:16:48.806 --> 00:16:50.725
One that we haven't seen before?

287
00:16:51.238 --> 00:16:54.166
That can rip the head
clean off a mako shark?

288
00:16:54.920 --> 00:16:58.200
Then I might have to cancel
my scuba trip next weekend.

289
00:17:23.968 --> 00:17:25.246
Hey!

290
00:17:25.271 --> 00:17:26.698
Are you okay?

291
00:17:29.763 --> 00:17:31.381
Do you need help?

292
00:17:48.395 --> 00:17:50.220
<i>Is she having trouble breathing?</i>

293
00:17:50.244 --> 00:17:52.444
No. no. no. her breathing's fine.

294
00:17:52.751 --> 00:17:54.362
Uh. a little heavy.

295
00:17:54.397 --> 00:17:55.982
<i>Okay. I'll head out now.</i>

296
00:17:56.007 --> 00:17:57.163
Are you sure?

297
00:17:57.198 --> 00:17:58.603
I mean. I'm happy to drive her

298
00:17:58.628 --> 00:18:00.200
down to the hospital in Port Angeles.

299
00:18:00.225 --> 00:18:01.653
<i> It's okay. Ben.</i>
<i>I'll meet you at your place.</i>

300
00:18:01.677 --> 00:18:03.250
Okay. All right. I'll see you there.

301
00:18:03.303 --> 00:18:05.101
Thanks. Dr. Abbott.

302
00:18:23.748 --> 00:18:25.780
Sorry. that's all I had.

303
00:18:42.142 --> 00:18:43.785
Littleneck clam.

304
00:18:43.847 --> 00:18:45.180
From Malakh Bay.

305
00:18:49.354 --> 00:18:51.587
You gonna say something?

306
00:18:58.424 --> 00:19:00.423
Now. I can help you.

307
00:19:01.271 --> 00:19:03.636
If you need to get back somewhere.

308
00:19:10.954 --> 00:19:12.820
You don't have to talk.

309
00:19:46.626 --> 00:19:49.591
That must be the... the doctor.

310
00:19:54.538 --> 00:19:56.014
Evening. Benjamin.

311
00:19:56.186 --> 00:19:57.628
She's in here.

312
00:19:58.687 --> 00:20:00.613
And kind of weird.

313
00:20:01.519 --> 00:20:02.998
Okay.

314
00:20:09.871 --> 00:20:11.232
She was right here.

315
00:20:16.823 --> 00:20:18.417
Slippery one. huh?

316
00:21:44.989 --> 00:21:47.912
- Give it to me?
- Uh. I think I'll keep it.

317
00:22:07.307 --> 00:22:09.034
Come inside! Have a look!

318
00:22:09.059 --> 00:22:12.084
The only real mermaid
artifacts in town!

319
00:22:12.196 --> 00:22:14.271
Come inside! Have a look!

320
00:22:14.357 --> 00:22:16.620
Maybe buy something while you're...

321
00:22:38.730 --> 00:22:40.691
Sorry. sorry. sorry.

322
00:22:43.446 --> 00:22:44.854
Ms. Hawkins.

323
00:22:45.705 --> 00:22:47.392
There was a girl just here.

324
00:22:47.803 --> 00:22:48.835
You saw her?

325
00:22:48.860 --> 00:22:50.848
Yeah. it looked like
you were talking to her.

326
00:22:52.511 --> 00:22:54.372
I... I didn't see anyone.

327
00:24:28.028 --> 00:24:29.179
Hey. Dad.

328
00:24:29.204 --> 00:24:31.163
- Hey.
- Good day at the office?

329
00:24:33.284 --> 00:24:34.909
You know Chris Mueller?

330
00:24:34.944 --> 00:24:36.395
Crews on Sean McClure's boat.

331
00:24:36.454 --> 00:24:37.602
Yeah. I know him.

332
00:24:37.627 --> 00:24:39.049
Got a call from his parents.

333
00:24:39.123 --> 00:24:41.284
Said he was medevaced
by a military chopper

334
00:24:41.309 --> 00:24:43.765
off Sean's boat in the strait.

335
00:24:44.281 --> 00:24:46.714
and now they can't find him.

336
00:24:47.368 --> 00:24:49.307
Got me calling every base
from here to Alaska

337
00:24:49.332 --> 00:24:51.225
looking for him.

338
00:24:51.250 --> 00:24:52.476
There's nothing.

339
00:24:52.501 --> 00:24:55.092
- So far.
- What do you think happened?

340
00:24:56.344 --> 00:24:57.984
I don't know.

341
00:25:04.478 --> 00:25:08.481
Creator. for this food and for You.

342
00:25:08.797 --> 00:25:10.476
we give thanks.

343
00:25:11.375 --> 00:25:12.896
And for Susan.

344
00:25:13.129 --> 00:25:15.229
may she find peace on her journey

345
00:25:15.332 --> 00:25:19.582
and within herself
and find her way back home.

346
00:25:25.489 --> 00:25:27.966
It's been eight months
since we've heard from her.

347
00:25:28.056 --> 00:25:30.714
Might be time to start dropping
her from the blessings.

348
00:25:31.644 --> 00:25:34.146
I believe your mother is being guided.

349
00:26:22.386 --> 00:26:23.876
Crash!

350
00:26:28.004 --> 00:26:29.930
♪ <i>I am Ryn</i> ♪

351
00:26:29.992 --> 00:26:31.647
♪ <i>And I live in the sea</i> ♪

352
00:26:31.734 --> 00:26:35.541
I... am... Ryn.

353
00:26:38.444 --> 00:26:40.404
Hello. Ryn.

354
00:26:50.062 --> 00:26:52.022
Hello. miss.

355
00:26:52.277 --> 00:26:54.136
I see you there.

356
00:26:55.057 --> 00:26:58.694
I... am... Ryn.

357
00:27:00.434 --> 00:27:02.308
Not from around here. are you?

358
00:27:03.556 --> 00:27:05.035
What you got?

359
00:27:05.274 --> 00:27:07.119
Helicopter?

360
00:27:24.072 --> 00:27:26.606
So. uh. you need a ride. huh?

361
00:27:27.102 --> 00:27:29.032
I'm headin' down to Aberdeen.

362
00:27:29.813 --> 00:27:31.028
Okay.

363
00:27:38.652 --> 00:27:41.376
Not much of a talker. huh?

364
00:27:44.166 --> 00:27:45.653
That's okay.

365
00:27:46.353 --> 00:27:48.233
It's nice just to have the company.

366
00:27:48.382 --> 00:27:49.807
Sometimes I'll pick up a hitcher.

367
00:27:49.832 --> 00:27:52.723
but. uh. they're mostly dudes.

368
00:27:53.337 --> 00:27:56.228
Not a pretty little thing like you.

369
00:28:00.606 --> 00:28:02.566
You like your little toy. huh?

370
00:28:39.970 --> 00:28:41.087
Hmm?

371
00:28:44.085 --> 00:28:45.646
You're like a little girl.

372
00:28:45.726 --> 00:28:48.003
A pretty little girl
who don't know how to talk.

373
00:28:50.933 --> 00:28:52.152
Now. I bet your mama told you.

374
00:28:52.177 --> 00:28:53.229
"Don't get into cars

375
00:28:53.254 --> 00:28:54.472
with strangers."

376
00:28:55.202 --> 00:28:57.509
But you didn't listen. Mm-mmm.

377
00:28:58.226 --> 00:29:00.568
You're a little rebel. huh? Yeah.

378
00:29:09.606 --> 00:29:11.333
Your skin's all dry.

379
00:29:11.536 --> 00:29:13.273
You ought to put some cream on that.

380
00:29:13.516 --> 00:29:15.533
make it nice and soft.

381
00:29:20.117 --> 00:29:22.249
Isn't that what you're
lookin' for? Huh?

382
00:29:23.435 --> 00:29:25.229
A little adventure?

383
00:29:25.549 --> 00:29:28.829
Little girl.
runnin' away from home. huh?

384
00:29:29.219 --> 00:29:31.184
Gettin' in a big man's car.

385
00:29:31.450 --> 00:29:32.930
Yeah.

386
00:29:34.061 --> 00:29:35.290
Yeah.

387
00:30:26.213 --> 00:30:28.173
Okay. guys. we're gonna go this way.

388
00:30:28.631 --> 00:30:30.258
Stay together. please.

389
00:30:30.283 --> 00:30:32.176
Watch your steps.

390
00:30:36.561 --> 00:30:38.016
This is not a zoo.

391
00:30:38.051 --> 00:30:39.887
This is a research and rescue center

392
00:30:39.912 --> 00:30:42.769
for the many marine mammals
that inhabit our region.

393
00:30:42.933 --> 00:30:44.974
We're able to offer veterinary care.

394
00:30:44.999 --> 00:30:47.993
perform surgical procedures.
and administer medication.

395
00:30:48.106 --> 00:30:49.958
What are all the TVs for?

396
00:30:49.998 --> 00:30:51.792
Those are so we can
keep an eye on our animals

397
00:30:51.816 --> 00:30:54.001
and what they're doing.
both in an out of the water.

398
00:30:55.640 --> 00:30:56.802
Yeah?

399
00:30:56.890 --> 00:30:58.350
When you were a kid.

400
00:30:58.400 --> 00:31:00.597
did you know you wanted to work here?

401
00:31:01.016 --> 00:31:02.924
Actually. it was a couple of years ago.

402
00:31:03.034 --> 00:31:05.959
I saw a video of a baby dolphin
that had washed ashore.

403
00:31:06.187 --> 00:31:08.017
Instead of helping it.
the people on the beach

404
00:31:08.057 --> 00:31:10.116
passed it around taking
their picture with it.

405
00:31:10.251 --> 00:31:12.795
Even after it died.
they kept taking selfies.

406
00:31:13.061 --> 00:31:15.660
That video made me sad.
and I wanted to do something.

407
00:31:15.768 --> 00:31:17.795
so I came here to volunteer.

408
00:31:18.083 --> 00:31:19.942
Now it's my job.

409
00:31:20.227 --> 00:31:22.303
You might be wondering
what our animals like to eat.

410
00:31:24.974 --> 00:31:26.295
Our fish shake...

411
00:31:26.329 --> 00:31:28.175
A delicious blend of herring and cod.

412
00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:30.687
with various nutrients
mixed in as well.

413
00:31:30.932 --> 00:31:32.313
Would anyone like a taste?

414
00:31:32.567 --> 00:31:33.828
No!

415
00:31:33.853 --> 00:31:35.169
No way.

416
00:31:35.194 --> 00:31:37.154
Okay. guys. we're gonna head outside.

417
00:31:54.470 --> 00:31:56.496
Whoa!

418
00:31:58.393 --> 00:32:00.092
- Whoa!
- Once our animals

419
00:32:00.117 --> 00:32:01.695
have received the medical
care they need.

420
00:32:01.720 --> 00:32:03.450
they come out here
to recover and prepare

421
00:32:03.475 --> 00:32:04.957
for their journey back to the wild.

422
00:32:05.010 --> 00:32:06.772
This is Sitka and Hazy.

423
00:32:23.249 --> 00:32:25.210
What's going on?

424
00:32:25.328 --> 00:32:26.692
I'm not sure.

425
00:32:32.920 --> 00:32:34.914
Everyone. come with me. Now.

426
00:32:37.015 --> 00:32:38.477
It was her! She did it!

427
00:32:38.633 --> 00:32:40.394
Come on!

428
00:32:53.544 --> 00:32:55.471
We meet again.

429
00:32:55.585 --> 00:32:56.914
It's okay.

430
00:32:57.351 --> 00:32:59.149
I'm not gonna hurt you.

431
00:32:59.769 --> 00:33:01.388
I can help you.

432
00:33:07.660 --> 00:33:09.238
My name is Ben.

433
00:33:10.499 --> 00:33:12.229
Friend.

434
00:33:18.338 --> 00:33:20.134
I am Ryn.

435
00:33:22.268 --> 00:33:23.563
Ryn.

436
00:33:24.319 --> 00:33:26.116
Okay.

437
00:33:26.784 --> 00:33:28.144
Good.

438
00:33:29.069 --> 00:33:30.722
It's nice to meet you.

439
00:33:30.754 --> 00:33:32.684
Where are you from?

440
00:33:32.709 --> 00:33:33.722
Hey.

441
00:33:33.747 --> 00:33:36.475
You're sick.

442
00:33:37.187 --> 00:33:39.552
Now. can I see?

443
00:33:45.600 --> 00:33:47.029
We have medication here.

444
00:33:47.904 --> 00:33:49.500
We can help you.

445
00:34:04.526 --> 00:34:07.010
The night we met. you sang a song.

446
00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:11.108
I can't get it out of my head.

447
00:34:11.628 --> 00:34:13.524
Everywhere I go...

448
00:34:13.957 --> 00:34:15.323
I hear it.

449
00:34:17.070 --> 00:34:18.435
Oh. hey.

450
00:34:18.507 --> 00:34:20.599
Um. everything's
back to normal out there.

451
00:34:20.624 --> 00:34:21.804
Not sure what that was all about.

452
00:34:23.569 --> 00:34:24.918
This is Ryn.

453
00:34:25.896 --> 00:34:27.565
I don't think she speaks English.

454
00:34:29.149 --> 00:34:30.562
Is she okay?

455
00:34:30.604 --> 00:34:32.026
I'm not sure.

456
00:34:32.219 --> 00:34:33.712
I was gonna call Doc Abbott.

457
00:34:33.737 --> 00:34:35.429
Yeah. Yeah. you should.

458
00:34:39.541 --> 00:34:40.991
You okay?

459
00:34:41.457 --> 00:34:43.473
Yeah. I guess.

460
00:34:44.049 --> 00:34:45.552
She's just...

461
00:34:45.601 --> 00:34:47.530
She's a little strange.

462
00:34:47.555 --> 00:34:49.022
You want me to stay?

463
00:34:49.047 --> 00:34:50.823
No. You got your class.

464
00:34:50.848 --> 00:34:51.907
It's okay.

465
00:34:51.932 --> 00:34:53.514
No. I don't want you to miss it.

466
00:34:53.646 --> 00:34:54.949
Okay. It's getting dark.

467
00:34:54.974 --> 00:34:56.732
I'm gonna lock down the pens.

468
00:34:58.888 --> 00:35:01.012
- I love you.
- Love you. too.

469
00:35:05.975 --> 00:35:08.168
I'm gonna call a doctor for you.

470
00:35:08.544 --> 00:35:09.931
Okay?

471
00:35:22.631 --> 00:35:24.560
Yeah. I'm pretty sure
we've got some of that.

472
00:35:24.630 --> 00:35:26.803
Bye. Thanks. Doc.
I'll see you in a bit.

473
00:38:22.798 --> 00:38:26.079
Whoa. easy there. Easy.

474
00:38:26.746 --> 00:38:28.117
What happened?

475
00:38:28.174 --> 00:38:29.304
Apparently one of the sea lions

476
00:38:29.329 --> 00:38:31.258
didn't like the herring
you served him for dinner.

477
00:38:31.283 --> 00:38:32.888
You should stay lying down. okay?

478
00:38:32.913 --> 00:38:34.711
Where is she?

479
00:38:35.252 --> 00:38:37.712
Ah. yes. your mystery date.

480
00:38:38.163 --> 00:38:41.125
Ben. I've know you and
your family a long time.

481
00:38:41.725 --> 00:38:44.044
Is there something
you're not telling me?

482
00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:00.952
Ms. Hawkins!

483
00:39:01.047 --> 00:39:02.310
Hello!

484
00:39:03.303 --> 00:39:04.301
Ms. Hawkins.

485
00:39:05.686 --> 00:39:07.679
That girl yesterday.

486
00:39:08.264 --> 00:39:09.794
I know you saw her.

487
00:39:10.121 --> 00:39:11.740
You said you didn't.
but I know you did.

488
00:39:11.764 --> 00:39:14.052
You know something about her.

489
00:39:15.074 --> 00:39:16.540
Come in.

490
00:39:24.866 --> 00:39:27.495
What is it you think I know?

491
00:39:27.903 --> 00:39:30.426
That she's one of them.

492
00:39:30.771 --> 00:39:33.389
I saw it. tonight.

493
00:39:33.710 --> 00:39:35.639
What did you see?

494
00:39:37.427 --> 00:39:40.322
She changed in the water.

495
00:39:44.058 --> 00:39:45.988
Just like this.

496
00:39:46.513 --> 00:39:48.874
When we were kids. we'd come in here.

497
00:39:48.899 --> 00:39:51.184
and you'd tell us stories
about the mermaids.

498
00:39:51.439 --> 00:39:52.928
We were always told that they were just

499
00:39:52.953 --> 00:39:54.404
tall tales. not to believe you.

500
00:39:54.429 --> 00:39:56.155
But they weren't made up. were they?

501
00:39:57.079 --> 00:39:58.642
They were true.

502
00:40:00.616 --> 00:40:01.947
I don't get it.

503
00:40:02.334 --> 00:40:04.300
You want people to know the truth.

504
00:40:04.885 --> 00:40:07.019
Well. it's here! It's happening!

505
00:40:07.044 --> 00:40:08.940
What are you so afraid of
all of a sudden?

506
00:40:09.692 --> 00:40:11.755
She do that to you?

507
00:40:15.272 --> 00:40:17.997
In their natural state in the water.

508
00:40:18.556 --> 00:40:20.162
they see you as prey.

509
00:40:21.189 --> 00:40:23.092
Their instinct is to kill.

510
00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:26.465
Humans never understood that.

511
00:40:26.990 --> 00:40:28.986
It caused a lot of misery.

512
00:40:29.785 --> 00:40:31.348
What do you mean?

513
00:40:31.607 --> 00:40:33.394
Your family's history in this town

514
00:40:33.419 --> 00:40:35.382
is bloodier than you know.

515
00:40:35.722 --> 00:40:39.477
Your ancestor lost his mind. obsessed.

516
00:40:40.051 --> 00:40:41.320
He and his shipmates slaughtered

517
00:40:41.351 --> 00:40:44.380
those beautiful creatures
in cold blood.

518
00:40:45.212 --> 00:40:46.976
Genocide.

519
00:40:48.237 --> 00:40:50.168
That's your legacy.

520
00:40:51.499 --> 00:40:54.494
Why don't you ask
your family about that?

521
00:41:47.663 --> 00:41:48.994
What's wrong. Mads?

522
00:41:49.500 --> 00:41:51.195
Just been trying to get a hold of Ben.

523
00:41:51.220 --> 00:41:52.466
He's not calling me back.

524
00:41:52.491 --> 00:41:54.418
Well. I'm sure he's just busy.

525
00:41:54.787 --> 00:41:57.560
See? There you go.

526
00:41:58.884 --> 00:42:00.223
Hello?

527
00:42:01.933 --> 00:42:03.862
Yeah. he's here.

528
00:42:04.185 --> 00:42:06.548
For you. it's Clarence.

529
00:42:08.075 --> 00:42:10.138
Hey. Clarence. what's up?

530
00:42:16.679 --> 00:42:18.112
Okay.

531
00:42:18.550 --> 00:42:19.844
All right.

532
00:42:20.042 --> 00:42:21.805
I'll be there.

533
00:42:24.266 --> 00:42:26.195
What's going on?

534
00:42:26.341 --> 00:42:27.751
They found a body.

535
00:42:27.823 --> 00:42:30.487
Some guy attacked in his car.

536
00:42:35.634 --> 00:42:38.429
Don't worry. He's gonna call you.

537
00:42:56.474 --> 00:42:57.837
Hey.

538
00:43:03.294 --> 00:43:04.495
What are you doing here?

539
00:43:04.539 --> 00:43:06.502
I'm coming with you.

540
00:43:12.923 --> 00:43:14.261
- Dad?
- Yeah?

541
00:43:16.308 --> 00:43:17.937
We got room for one more?

